Ingredients:
1 pound of chicken tenders
Cajun seasoning
Creole seasoning 
1 jalapeño 
Garlic purée 
Sundried tomatoes
Pasta of your choice
Parmesan cheese 
1 cup of heavy cream
Salt to taste

Directions:
Cook pasta per package directions but reserve half a cup of the pasta water
Season chicken with copious amounts of the seasonings 
Sauté chicken until cooked thru, has a beautiful crust, and left a flavorful fond
In the fond, sauté a teaspoon of garlic purée then add your diced jalapeño and sundried tomatoes 
Deglaze the pan with the pasta water, add some heavy cream and season once more
Add an unthinkable amount of Parmesan cheese to the sauce and let thicken
Toss the pasta and the chicken back into the pan and stir 
Plate up with more cheese, say bismillah, and enjoy!

@nick.digiovanni Challenged me for a Chicken and Rice off, who won? 🤤

Chicken Mandi 

Ingredients:
1 whole chicken
3 cups basmati rice
2 shallots
2 jalapenos
2 bay leaves
A few cardamom pods
Ghee/clarified butter 
1 teaspoon garlic paste
1 teaspoon ginger paste
Spice Mix:
¼ teaspoon Cumin
1 teaspoon Cayenne pepper
½ teaspoon Ground clove
2 teaspoons Turmeric
½ teaspoon Coriander seed
½ teaspoon Cinnamon 
½ teaspoon Ground ginger
1 teaspoon Allspice
1 teaspoon Ground cardamom 
Salsa:
2 bunches of cilantro
2 tomatoes
2 jalapenos
A few cloves of garlic
1 tablespoon of olive oil
Salt to taste

Directions: 
In a bowl combine 2 tablespoons of ghee, the garlic and ginger pastes, salt and pepper to taste, and 1 tablespoon of the spice mix
Remove the spine from the chicken then rub with the spice paste
In an oven safe pot, saute the shallots and jalapenos, add 1 tablespoon of the spice mix, bay leaves and cardamom pods in a 2 tablespoons of ghee
Once everything is toasted and aromatic, add the washed rice, mix, and add water
*add a few extra tablespoons of water than what's listed on the package since more moisture is going to be lost in the oven
Place a wire over the rice pot and lay the chicken on top of that. This allows all those flavorful drippings to get caught in the rice
Bake at 375 for roughly 50 minutes to 1 hour but make sure to check the internal temperature since cooking time may vary depending on the size of the chicken
*If you want to smoke the chicken/rice, drop the chicken into the pot, place a heat proof bowl with a few tablespoons of oil in there as well, drop a charcoal and cover
For the salsa, rough chop the vegetables then blend with the rest of the ingredients
Plate up the rice, place the chicken on top, salsa to the side, say bismillah, and enjoy!

node.text:
Chicken & Rice 😍

Vinaigrette: 

3 lemons juice and zest 
2 Tbsp vinegar 
1/4 cup olive oil 
Pinch of salt 
1 Tbsp Dijon (I used alcohol free)
Optional: garlic 

4 chicken legs with 1/2 the Vinaigrette 
1 tsp sazon and lemon pepper (season to preference) 

Oven bake at 375F for 30-40 minutes until 170 infernal 

Rice: 
2 cups preferred grained rice 
Follow the liquid amount for the rice with chicken stock 
2 Tbsp butter 
1/2 tsp saffron bloomed In hot water 
Salt to taste (1-2 tsp)

Salad:
2 Persian cucumbers 
1 tomato 
1/2 shallot 
1 jalapeño 
Cilantro and mint to taste 
Salt to taste ( I did 1 tsp)

Finish with a bit of the vinaigrette on the salad and top it off for a zing 😇

My Favorite Spaghetti 🤤

10oz Spaghetti 
4 Large tomatoes 
1 medium onion 
1 jalapeño 
1/4 cup olive oil 
5 cloves garlic 
Salt to taste (I did around 1 Tbsp)
Spices I used: 1tsp of garlic , onion, paprika, chili, cayenne 
1 lb ground beef (optional) 

Simmer the sauce down to about 1/2 the starting amount. It took me about 20-30 minutes 

Finish with cheese if you’re feeling wild.
